cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite both this repository and the parent research program's pre-registration (OSF DOI 10.17605/OSF.IO/Q6JYN)."
title: "kiki-flow-research: A Wasserstein Gradient Flow Engine for LLM Consolidation"
abstract: >
  kiki-flow-research is the upstream Wasserstein-gradient-flow engine
  used by the dreamOfkiki research program to model knowledge
  consolidation on continual-learning substrates. It provides the
  numerical routines (species ontology, flow integrators, divergence
  estimators, benchmark harness) that the downstream substrates
  (kiki-oniric MLX, E-SNN thalamocortical) depend on. Grounded in the
  Levelt-Baddeley model of language production, with a species
  decomposition spanning phonological, lexical, syntactic, and
  semantic levels.
